    "description": "Japan Data Science Consortium Co.Ltd., operates an AI tech company, develops algorithm modules utilizing machine learning in Japan. The company operates through AI solutions business, financial advisory business, and marketing support business segments. The company provides Wodom! A data platform for building data infrastructure and BI (Business Intelligence) dashboards in SaaS format; learning insight; home insight, a home IoT that solves social issues, such as nursing care prevention and reduction of absentee deliveries; demand insight, an AI solution that prevents stockout and overstock, and semi-automates ordering operations; and maintenance insight, an AI solution that realizes remote monitoring, anomaly detection, and operation optimization of manufacturing equipment and home appliances. It is also involved in the development and operation of IT systems; technical services; and data science advisory and consulting business, as well as in project management. Japan Data Science Consortium Co.Ltd. was founded in 2013 and is based in Tokyo, Japan."
